  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;Overview of care and treatment&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Susan MacLean&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;The Overview of the department. All staff, from receptionists, porters, doctors, consultants and nurses were exemplary. I was treated with respect and utmost professionalism. My concerns are the facilities within the waiting rooms.
Too few chairs to accommodate those who are ill waiting to be seen. Not enough information. Some of those attending are stressed and unsure what to do or where to go. My suggestions.
More seating. Large straight forward signs. Booking in given a number allocated to name. Screen showing name and number when ready to go through for treatment. I couldn't hear names being called over the hubbub. TV screens showing news or TV to calm those waiting. Free water fountain. Free charging points for phones. Air conditioning it was too hot. When windows open too cold. Distinctive uniforms. Volunteers walking around the waiting room checking if anyone needed assistance. The room and toilets need constant attention with a good clean. The toilet when I visited was disgusting and blood on the floor tissues everywhere a health hazard in itself.
If possible the room should be remodeled where access to treatment is through one secure door not three to my knowledge. This would keep staff safe. 
I am hoping this is a positive response and changes can be considered.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
